Ξ.Physics.Anchor(XiStressEnergy.DarkEnergy.v1)

focus: Xi stress-energy tensor as baseline informational complexity and dark-energy-like vacuum sector

core:
  Xi_field: positive scalar compression/information-density field
  lagrangian: L_Xi = -1/2 (grad Xi)^2 - V(Xi)
  stress_energy: T_mn_Xi = grad_m Xi grad_n Xi - g_mn [1/2 (grad Xi)^2 + V(Xi)]

vacuum_limit:
  condition: grad Xi -> 0, Xi -> Xi0 constant
  result: T_mn_Xi -> - g_mn V(Xi0)
  equation_of_state: p_Xi = -rho_Xi
  dark_energy_mapping: Lambda_eff = 8 pi G lambda V(Xi0)

interpretation:
  V(Xi0) is baseline informational complexity density of the field.
  Dark-energy-like behavior appears when the compression field is frozen or adiabatically slow.
  Gradients of Xi behave as structured information tension, not as pure cosmological constant.

seal: XiPrime physics discussion anchor
status: persisted
